<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: CHEATING IS COMMON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Youth News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 According to the 24th annual survey of high achievers conducted by Who's Who 
Among American High School Students, 80% of the teens interviewed said cheating 
is common in their school. 
</P>
<P>
 Seventy-eight percent of about 500 teens interviewed added that they 
themselves have cheated. The most common form of cheating, according to the 
survey, is copying someone else's homework. Of the teens interviewed, all of 
whom are considered high achievers, 67% admitted to copying homework; 14% 
admitted to plagiarizing part of an essay. 
</P>
<P>
 A reason teens cheat, according to the survey, is self-imposed pressure and 
pressure from parents to do well in school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
