<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: A TOUGH STAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Parent, Teacher, Student Assn. at Esperanza High School in Anaheim says it 
is alarmed at the growing number of alcohol and drug-related parties that 
students apparently are attending at homes in Yorba Linda, Placentia and 
northeast Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 As a result, the PTSA has passed a resolution urging local law enforcement 
agencies to make it a policy to notify homeowners when police become aware that 
a party involving alcohol and minors has occurred in the home. The group is 
also urging all parents to take a zero tolerance stand against alcohol or drug 
use by Esperanza students and has called on all local merchants who sell 
alcoholic beverages to demand proof of age to reduce the potential for purchase 
by minors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
