<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE BLOTTER; AROUND THE VALLEY . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ARCADIA: A robber held up the World Savings and Loan at 1200 S. Baldwin Ave. 
about 3:45 p.m. Jan. 13 and made off with roughly $200. The robber was 
described as a black-haired white male about 50 years of age, 5 feet 6 inches 
tall, 165 pounds, with a limp. 
</P>
<P>
 AZUSA: A burglary was reported to police at 2:30 p.m. Monday in the 800 block 
of South Cerritos Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 BALDWIN PARK: A residential burglary was reported to police about noon Sunday 
in the 400 block of East Eighth Street.  
</P>
<P>
 CLAREMONT: Two men were arrested during a residential burglary about 9:35 a.m. 
Jan. 13 after a neighbor saw them forcing open the front door of a house in the 
400 block of St. Bonaventure Street, said Lt. Gary Jenkins. Arrested were Todd 
Ollis, 29, of Upland and Matthew Holzinger, 29, of Fontana. Officers discovered 
about $3,500 in jewelry, computers and CDs stacked in the front entryway of the 
house. 
</P>
<P>
 COVINA: A 23-year-old man was stabbed Jan. 13 in what he described as a 
"set-up" at the Jack-in-the-Box at 1052 N. Grand Ave., Sgt. Mark Corder said. 
Covina resident Eric Carlisle said his female companion persuaded him to drive 
to the restaurant, where he suffered minor knife wounds after five men jumped 
him. He had been involved in a fight with several of his attackers Dec. 31, 
Corder said. 
</P>
<P>
 LA VERNE: A white Chevrolet Suburban was reported stolen from in front of the 
house at 571 Lavender St. about 5:20 Friday morning, said Lt. Paul Allen. No 
arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 MONROVIA: A residential burglary was reported to Monrovia police at 12:11 a.m. 
Sunday in the 200 block of South Shamrock Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: A dispute between two roommates in the first block of Cedar Street 
escalated into physical violence Sunday night when one man banged the other's 
head against the floor and kicked him in the face, police said. Officers 
responded to the call about 12:30 a.m. One roommate was hospitalized with minor 
injuries. No arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A Pomona man is in critical condition at County-USC Medical Center 
after being shot in the head early Friday morning at the Pala Motel. Willie J. 
Lester, about 30, who lives in the motel at 987 E. Holt St., was found shot in 
the head near his room about 6:30 a.m. and airlifted by helicopter to the 
medical center. Detectives are investigating. 
</P>
<P>
 TEMPLE CITY: A fire in a camper shell might have killed a 38-year-old Temple 
City man in the early morning Jan. 13, Los Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Gabe 
Ramirez reported. Firefighters responded to the blaze about 2:30 a.m. and found 
the man's body among the debris of the camper, Ramirez said. The cause of the 
fire and the death are under investigation. The man's name was withheld until 
his family could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
 WEST COVINA: A Rowland Heights construction worker linked to a dozen photos 
that showed a 4-year-old girl being molested has pleaded no contest to eight 
counts of lewd conduct with a child. Paul Lynn Loe, 46, who entered the plea 
Jan. 13 in Citrus Municipal Court, faces a possible 20-year prison term when he 
is formally sentenced Jan. 27 in Pomona Superior Court. He was arrested Dec. 31 
after the photos of Loe and the child were found in a Whittier garbage bin. As 
part of a plea bargain with the district attorney's office, two other lewd 
conduct counts and five counts of child pornography were dropped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
