<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: ALTADENA; PSYCHOLOGIST SENTENCED FOR MOLESTING BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Altadena psychologist has been sentenced to five years in prison for 
molesting his foster son and another boy. 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Mercer, a 44-year-old former foster parent and teacher of 
learning-disabled children, was described as a "Jekyll and Hyde" character by 
Pasadena Superior Court Judge Thomas W. Stoever, who handed down the sentence 
last Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mercer was convicted Dec. 22 of nine counts of oral copulation and lewd 
conduct with adolescent boys. 
</P>
<P>
 All the incidents occurred between 1990 and 1992. His two victims, who were 14 
and 15 in 1992, were his students at Marianne Frostig Center for Educational 
Therapy. The boys reported the molestation to a center official in June. 
</P>
