</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 La Quinta stopped Rancho Alamitos' 47-game Garden Grove League winning streak 
in girls' basketball with a 64-60 victory at Rancho Alamitos Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior guard Linda Rodriguez and sophomore forward Rhonda Gondringer combined 
for 58 of La Quinta's 64 points.Rodriguez made six three-pointers, scoring a 
game-high 33 points and Gondringer added 25 for the Aztecs (12-4, 6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos' leading scorer Akilah Rodgers struggled. She was held 
scoreless in the first half and finished the game with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Frank, the Vaqueros second leading scorer who injured her ankle in a 
game with Kennedy, attempted to play in the second quarter but was unable to 
run. Sally Vasquez and Detra Vickers added 10 points each for Rancho Alamitos 
(11-6, 5-1). 
