<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPIRE LEAGUE BOYS' BASKETBALL; NO. 2 LOS ALAMITOS BLASTS NO. 10 ESPERANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If Esperanza is the best challenger the Empire League can muster for Los 
Alamitos, perhaps the Griffins' remaining league games will be merely tune-ups 
for the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos, ranked second in Orange County, blasted No. 10 Esperanza, 69-41, 
in an Empire League boys' basketball game Wednesday at Los Alamitos High, and 
it wasn't even that close. 
</P>
<P>
 Tim Lin had 15 points, including three three-pointers, and Brady Doyle added 
14 to lead Los Alamitos (16-3, 4-0 in league), which scored the first 12 points 
of the game and led by as many as 32 points in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza (12-7, 2-2) didn't score until Josh Greer made an 18-foot jumper, 
the Aztecs' lone basket of the first quarter, with 1 minute 58 seconds 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos' defense frustrated the Aztecs into 21 turnovers, while forcing 
them to shoot 17% (four of 23) from the field in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Ali Ton and Lin took turns hounding Esperanza's Mike Thimgan, who entered the 
game averaging 14 points, and their denial defense held Thimgan to three points 
and just five shots in the first half while the Griffins built a 36-14 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Thimgan didn't get his hands on the ball in the Esperanza offense until the 
first quarter was nearly halfway finished. 
</P>
<P>
 Offensively, Ton set the pace dishing out 10 assists to go with his seven 
points. Forward Ryan Staniec, who had 11 points and 12 rebounds, was one of 
Ton's many beneficiaries as the Griffins scored 40 of their 57 points in the 
paint during the first three quarters. Los Alamitos shot 51% (24 of 47) through 
three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 "Ali set the pace on offense and we got a lot of good opportunities in 
transition," Los Alamitos Coach Steve Brooks said. "They executed well 
tonight." 
</P>
<P>
 Thimgan had 11 points and 10 rebounds and Greer had eight points and four 
blocked shots to lead Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
 In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 50, Cypress 41 -- Nick Roditis scored 16 points for host Katella 
(11-6, 2-2). LaBryon Clayton added 13 and Mike Pahl 11 for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Boberg scored 19 points for Cypress (11-8, 2-2), which led, 15-9, at the 
end of the first quarter. Katella then outscored Cypress, 11-3, to take a 20-18 
lead at the half.  
</P>
<P>
 Katella, Esperanza and Cypress are tied for second, two games behind Los 
Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 63, Loara 49 -- Dante Spencer scored 22 points and Dustin Miller and 
Jeff Moore each added 12 to lead El Dorado (6-11, 1-3).  
</P>
<P>
 Scott Davis scored 19 points for Loara (11-8, 1-3), which started well, 
leading, 17-13, at the end of the first quarter. Ed Dorado then outscored 
Loara, 30-20, over the next two quarters. 
</P>
