<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; FOBBS' FREE THROWS SPARK TRABUCO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laquent Fobbs made two free throws with two seconds left in the second 
overtime to give Trabuco Hills an 84-82 victory over Laguna Hills in a Pacific 
Coast League boys' basketball game Wednesday at Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 A full-court shot by a Laguna Hills player missed at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 Fobbs scored 11 points, Nick Punto added 22, including six three-pointers, and 
Ryan Karnoff had 21 as No. 4 Trabuco Hills (16-4, 4-0) remained alone in first 
place. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Scaglione, who had 18 points for Laguna Hills, tied the score with a 
three-pointer with a minute left in the first overtime, and Laguna Hills had a 
chance to win when Alex Hale was fouled with six seconds left. But Hale, who 
finished with 16 points and 18 rebounds, missed both free throws. Jason Charles 
added 18 points for Laguna Hills (7-10, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Pacific Coast League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Century 59, Estancia 49 -- Thomas Harmon scored 23 points for ninth-ranked 
Century (17-3, 3-1). Clay Frenz led visiting Estancia (11-8, 2-2) with 11 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 52, Costa Mesa 51 -- The Artists made five of six free throws in 
the last two minutes to hold on. Ryan Steck missed a 12-foot turnaround jumper 
at the buzzer for Costa Mesa (6-12, 0-4). Ian McDonald scored 21 points for 
Laguna Beach (5-13, 1-3). 
</P>
