<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOWLING; HIMMLER LEADS IN LAKEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON SNYDER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cincinnati's Brian Himmler built a 12-game total of 2,769 to take the lead 
after two rounds of the AC/Delco PBA Tournament at Cal Bowl in Lakewood. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Hoskins of Tarpon Springs, Fla., had opened a first-round lead earlier 
Wednesday, bowling games of 247, 238, 235, 224, 236 and 234 for a total of 
1,414. 
</P>
<P>
 But Hoskins slipped slightly off the pace in the second round as Himmler 
rolled games of 226, 246, 268, 248, 248 and 246 to take a 2,769-2,761 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Joe Firpo of Lakewood, Fla., is in third place at 2,754. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first round, Atlanta's Brian Voss rolled a perfect game before a packed 
audience, but cheers were silenced at about 1:12 p.m. when aftershocks rocked 
the center. DON SNYDER 
</P>
</TEXT>
