<P>
 The New York Mets, unable to make a trade for a shortstop, agreed to a 
$425,000, one-year contract with free agent Luis Rivera. 
</P>
<P>
 Rivera batted .208 with one home run and seven runs batted in in 62 games for 
the Boston Red Sox last season and made $1,075,000.His season was shortened 
because of two stints on the disabled list because of a strained lower left rib 
cage and an injured right hamstring. College Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 A college basketball doubleheader honoring former UCLA coach John Wooden and 
scheduled for Dec. 4 at the 18,300-seat Anaheim Arena will include UCLA, 
Kansas, Kentucky and Massachusetts. 
</P>
<P>
 Randy Ryan of Santa Margarita, an official of Group W Broadcasting of New 
York, said that his organization would run the event and said the matchups 
would be UCLA against Kentucky and Kansas against Massachusetts. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan said the John R. Wooden Classic, which Group W hopes will be an annual 
event, would be telecast on a major network to be announced soon. Sailing  
