<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Quinn, an assistant junior varsity coach at Mater Dei, was suspended two 
games for fighting after the Monarchs' game against Dana Hills on Jan. 7, Mater 
Dei Principal Lyle Porter said. 
</P>
<P>
 David Dickens, the Dana Hills' assistant coach who was involved in the 
altercation, has written letters of apology to officials at both schools and to 
Quinn, Dana Hills Athletic Director Rich Skelton said. Skelton said no further 
action was taken because the school's investigation determined Dickens was not 
the instigator. 
