</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Cal State Fullerton volleyball Coach Jim Huffman's $1.2 million 
wrongful termination suit against the school went to trial, with jurors hearing 
attorneys' opening statements and testimony from Titan women's gymnastics Coach 
Lynn Rogers in Orange County Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Huffman claims his firing in 1992 was in retaliation "because he spoke out 
about illegalities in the CSUF athletic department and initiated successful 
(gender equity) legal proceedings, which resulted in negative publicity to the 
school and its administrators." 
</P>
<P>
 Defense attorney Kevin Gerry will argue that Huffman was let go because of 
poor performance. 
</P>
