<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; COUPLE WILL BE HONORED AS YMCA CITIZENS 
OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Richard Rosenzweig, chairman of the Beverly Hills Visitors Bureau, and his 
wife, Judy Henning, have been named Citizens of the Year by the Beverly Hills 
Family YMCA. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple, who have been residents of the city for 17 years, will be honored 
for their civic and cultural contributions at the Family Y's annual gala dinner 
March 9 at the Beverly Hilton Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosenzweig, who is executive vice president of Playboy Enterprises, will be 
recognized for his civic involvement and efforts to promote the city. Henning, 
a public relations consultant, will also be honored for her community 
involvement and her work with the Los Angeles County Museum of Art and the 
Museum of Contemporary Art. 
</P>
