<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: SFUZZI AND CAYMUS VINEYARD TO TEAM UP ON 4-COURSE MEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sfuzzi in Costa Mesa is playing host to Caymus Vineyard on Monday for a dinner 
accompanied by the vineyard's wines. The four-course meal, which begins at 7 
p.m., is $45 per person, plus tax and tip. Among the courses are a warm salmon 
and leek tart with roasted tomatoes and arugula, paired with Caymus Conundrum 
1992; and pan-seared veal medallions with sage, Romano potatoes and red onion 
cherry confit, with Caymus Cabernet Sauvignon, special select, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 1870-A Harbor Blvd. (714) 548-9500. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Diners can share a table with some of the area's French chefs on Monday night 
at 6:30 at Pascal. 
