<HEADLINE>
<P>
JERROLD A. FADEM; CONDEMNATION LAW EXPERT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerrold (Jerry) A. Fadem, 67, nationally known Los Angeles legal authority on 
condemnation. A native of St. Louis, Fadem studied at Washington University and 
graduated from UCLA in industrial management, later earning his law degree from 
Loyola University.He established a reputation and expertise in condemnation 
litigation by winning damages for homeowners who were unable to sell their 
homes because of airplane noise at Los Angeles International Airport. He went 
on to represent homeowners in litigation with government agencies over 
landslides, coastal zone restrictions, drainage of lakes and other problems 
diminishing their property values. Throughout his career, Fadem tried more than 
200 condemnation cases in California and 14 other states. He chaired the State 
Bar of California's Committee on Condemnation Law and Procedure, and was a 
popular lecturer and author on the subject. On Jan. 13 in Los Angeles of a 
cerebral hemorrhage. 
</P>
