<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; NURSING CENTER WILL HOLD LECTURE SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beverly Manor Nursing Center-Westminster will hold the first in a series of 
monthly lectures on health and health care issues today at Beverly Manor, 240 
Hospital Circle. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-hour lecture, starting at noon, will deal with preventing falls.It 
will be conducted by the center's therapists and nurses. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is free, but reservations are required. To make reservations, call 
the Community Relations Department at (714) 892-6686. 
</P>
<P>
 The Feb. 17 lecture will deal with health care reform and how it will affect 
people. 
</P>
<P>
 On March 24, the topic is nutrition. On April 20, the focus will be on home 
safety and participants will be shown how to eliminate potential risks in their 
homes. 
</P>
<P>
 A free hearing screening will follow the May 19 lecture on hearing and 
communications. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
