SOUTHBAY / COMMUNITY NEWS: TORRANCE; LIBRARY BOOKS MAY BE RENEWED BY PHONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the first time, Torrance Library patrons may renew books by telephone. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrons may call the library on a touch-tone phone and use a new automated 
computer system to find a book's due day, renew it and determine if any overdue 
fines are owed. 
</P>
<P>
 The library expects hundreds of calls a week, said Norm Reeder, library 
programs administrator. 
</P>
<P>
 The system, which serves the city's six libraries, was funded with a $20,000 
donation from the nonprofit Friends of the Library.  
</P>
<P>
 In several months, the system will call patrons automatically when materials 
are overdue or requested books have arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 Such calls will save the library about $6,500 a year in mailing costs, Reeder 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The number to renew books is (310) 618-2785 or 2786. 
</P>
