<P>
MIGHTY BOSSTONES CAFE SHOW CANCELED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM and RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Jan. 27 concert at the Rhythm Cafe by the Mighty Mighty Bosstones, a 
ska-rock band from Boston, has been canceled. 
</P>
<P>
 The show had been booked by an outside promoter, Paul Tollett of Goldenvoice 
Presents, who said Wednesday that he decided to cancel because of uncertainty 
over the Rhythm Cafe's future.The club's landlord has filed papers in Orange 
County Superior Court seeking to have the current Cafe management evicted for 
non-payment of rent. 
</P>
<P>
 Tollett said Tony Cardullo, who has been trying to coordinate Cafe bookings, 
told him last week that the club was having "license problems" and advised him 
to switch the show to another location, but there was not enough time. Cardullo 
could not be reached.  
</P>
<P>
 Tickets to the show will be refunded at points of purchase. MIKE BOEHM and 
RICK VANDERKNYFF 
</P>
