<P>
PEDESTRIAN, 18, CRITICALLY WOUNDED IN SHOOTING LAID TO GANG ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old pedestrian was shot in the head Wednesday in what police said 
was a gang-related attack. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Benjamin Silva Torivio of Santa Ana, was reported in critical 
condition at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Torivio and a companion were walking west in the 400 block of East Vance 
Street near the intersection of French Street, when a small pickup truck 
passed, Lt. Bob Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 100 yards away, the truck stopped and the passenger got out and fired a 
handgun three times in the direction of the pedestrians, witnesses told police. 
One of the shots hit Torivio in the head. 
</P>
<P>
 There was no conversation between the pedestrians and the two men in the 
truck, witnesses said, and the pickup sped away. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are investigating the shooting as gang-related, Helton said. The pickup 
truck is described as a dark red or maroon Nissan or Toyota with primer on the 
driver's door, left front fender and tailgate. 
</P>
