<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE / THE LONG ROAD BACK; DRIVERS BEWARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Transportation officials added new closures to the commuter grid Wednesday as 
thousands of Southland commuters struggle to find new routes: Roads 
</P>
<P>
 The following roads are closed: 
</P>
<P>
 1. Pacific Coast Highway, from Chautauqua Boulevard to Temescal Canyon because 
of landslide. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Northbound: From Pacific Coast Highway, right on Chautauqua 
(north), then left (west) on Sunset Boulevard, left (south) on Temescal Canyon 
Road back to northbound Pacific Coast Highway. Southbound: Two lanes open. 
</P>
<P>
 2. Golden State Freeway (I-5) northbound, closed at Antelope Valley Freeway 
(14) because of bridge damage, but truck lane to Antelope Valley Freeway is 
open. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Take northbound Antelope Valley Freeway to San Fernando 
Road (Route 126), left on Lyons Avenue to the Golden State Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 3. The southbound Golden State Freeway (I-5) is closed between Lyons Avenue 
and the Foothill Freeway (210) because of bridge collapse. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Lyons Avenue, east to San Fernando Road, south on 
Sierra Highway to San Fernando Road, south on Sepulveda Boulevard to Roxford 
Street to I-5. 
</P>
<P>
 4. Golden State Freeway (I-5) southbound, north of Route 138, closed from 
Lyons Avenue to the Foothill Freeway (210) because of bridge collapse. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Golden State (I-5) southbound to Route 138 (eastbound) to 
the Antelope Valley Freeway (Route 14) to eastbound Route 138 to Interstate 15. 
Use westbound Santa Monica Freeway (I-10) or the Pomona Freeway (60) to 
Downtown L.A. 
</P>
<P>
 5. The eastbound Santa Monica Freeway (I-10) is closed from the San Diego 
Freeway (405) to Washington Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Take eastbound Pico Boulevard, then right on La Brea to 
eastbound Santa Monica Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 6. The westbound Santa Monica Freeway is closed from Washington Boulevard to 
La Cienega Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Washington Boulevard, proceed to Fairfax Avenue, 
left at Venice Boulevard, right at Cadillac Avenue, left at La Cienega 
Boulevard to westbound Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 7. The westbound Santa Monica Freeway connector to the southbound San Diego 
Freeway (405) is closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Westbound traffic exit at Overland Boulevard, proceed 
straight onto National Boulevard to southbound San Diego Freeway (405) on-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
 8. Antelope Valley Freeway (14) northbound lanes 3 and 4 are closed between 
the Golden State Freeway (I-5) split and San Fernando Road. Primary alternate: 
Not required. 
</P>
<P>
 9. Antelope Valley Freeway (14) southbound closed at Placerita Canyon Road 
(before the Golden State Freeway interchange). 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit southbound Antelope Valley Freeway (14) at Placerita 
Canyon Road, left (southbound) on Sierra Highway which turns to San Fernando 
Road, proceed south to Sepulveda Boulevard, right on Sepulveda Boulevard to 
Roxford Street, proceed to southbound Golden State Freeway (I-5). 
</P>
<P>
 10. Hollywood Freeway (101) connector northbound at Route 170 has one of three 
lanes closed because of structural damage. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Two lanes open on northbound Hollywood Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 11. Eastbound Simi Valley Freeway (118) is closed from Reseda Boulevard to 
Foothill Freeway (210). 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit onto southbound De Soto Avenue or Tampa Avenue to 
Devonshire Street, left on Devonshire Street to southbound San Diego Freeway or 
right on Arleta Avenue, left on Van Nuys Boulevard to the Golden State Freeway 
or the Foothill Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 12. Westbound Simi Valley Freeway (118) is closed from the Foothill Freeway 
(210) to Reseda Boulevard. All connectors from the Golden State and Foothill 
freeways to the Simi Valley Freeway (118) are also closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: From northbound San Diego Freeway, exit at Roscoe Boulevard 
or Devonshire Street, left to Tampa Avenue or De Soto Avenue, right to 
westbound Simi Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 13. All connectors from the westbound Foothill Freeway to the westbound Simi 
Valley Freeway are closed.  
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Westbound Foothill Freeway, exit on Foothill Boulevard, 
westbound to Van Nuys Boulevard to northbound Arleta Avenue, proceed westbound 
on Devonshire Street, northbound on Tampa Avenue or De Soto Avenue to the Simi 
Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 14. All connectors from the westbound Foothill Freeway to the northbound 
Golden State Freeway are closed. Westbound Foothill Freeway (210) is closed at 
Yarnell Street. The Golden State Freeway (I-5) northbound connector to the 
eastbound Foothill Freeway (210) is closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit Foothill Freeway on Roxford Boulevard, proceed 
westbound to Golden State Freeway (I-5), northbound Golden State Freeway via 
truck route to northbound Antelope Valley Freeway to westbound San Fernando 
Road, left on Lyons Avenue to the Golden State Freeway (I-5). 
</P>
<P>
 15. The northbound San Diego Freeway (405) is closed at Devonshire Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Nordhoff Street, east on Nordhoff Street/Osborne 
Street to the Golden State Freeway (I-5) northbound. 
</P>
<P>
 16. The northbound San Diego Freeway connector to the westbound Simi Valley 
Freeway is closed. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit at Nordhoff Street, west to Tampa Avenue, then north 
to westbound Simi Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 17. The southbound San Diego Freeway is closed at Rinaldi Street because of a 
buckled freeway structure. 
</P>
<P>
 Primary alternate: Exit right on Rinaldi Street to Reseda Boulevard, proceed 
to westbound Simi Valley Freeway on-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
 For freeway information, call (800) 427-7623 Rail 
</P>
<P>
 Amtrak service between Los Angeles and San Luis Obispo will resume today. 
Santa Barbara-to-Los Angeles line resumed service Wednesday. Call (800) 
USA-RAIL for information. Mass Transit 
</P>
<P>
 MTA bus lines, including the Blue Line trains and Red Line subway, are in full 
service. There will be intermittent detours as workers clear earthquake damage 
on the following bus lines: 
</P>
<P>
 Line 90: Los Angeles, Sunland and Sylmar (via Pennsylvania Avenue) 
</P>
<P>
 Line 94: Los Angeles, San Fernando, Sylmar (via San Fernando Road) 
</P>
<P>
 Line 236: From Ventura Boulevard to Rinaldi Street and north/south on Woodley 
Avenue and Balboa Boulevard 
</P>
<P>
 Line 243: From Woodland Hills along Ventura Boulevard to Winnetka Avenue 
</P>
<P>
 Line 634 has been established from the Malibu-Santa Monica area to Downtown 
Los Angeles. Buses have been added to five Westside lines and one line in the 
San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (213) 244-6347, (818) 781-5860 or (818) 246-2593.  
</P>
<P>
 Metrolink: The Santa Clarita Valley line will be extended to the Antelope 
Valley with four new stations scheduled to open in the next few weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Caltrans  
</P>
