<P>
 Ralphs supermarkets -- A story in Tuesday's editions about shortages of vital 
goods after Monday's earthquake incorrectly reported that a Ralphs store in 
Northridge sold a 2.5-gallon container of drinking water for $2, while a Ralphs 
in Granada Hills sold the same size container for $5. The grocery chain said $5 
was the price paid for a box containing two 2.5-gallon jugs. Ralphs said the 
two stores, which were damaged in the quake, were open only to sell emergency 
items as a service to the community. 
</P>
