<TEXT>
<P>
 New judges -- A Jan. 11 article on new judges said that according to Justice 
Department officials, Judge Martha A. Vasquez of New Mexico was the first 
Mexican-American woman appointed to the federal bench. In fact, U.S. District 
Judge Irma E. Gonzalez, whose parents were both Mexican, was appointed by 
President George Bush and sits on the federal bench in San Diego. 
</P>
